          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 20670,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The Nordic business community stresses identifying true legal gaps, rather than enforcement gaps, before proposing legal measures in a Digital Fairness Act. Improved cooperation between national authorities and the EU Commission is required for effective enforcement. Any new legislation must be evidence-based, proportionate, and technology-neutral.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s1",
          "section_path": [
            "Joint comments from Nordic business federations to a Digital Fairness Act"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 45,
          "char_len": 350
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p9",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "tackling unethical techniques and commercial practices"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 13928,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The European Commission has announced that it will propose a Digital Fairness Act to reinforce consumer protection in a targeted manner, making the principles in existing consumer protection rules more concrete and filling the identified gaps by tackling unethical techniques and commercial practices and strengthening consumer rights.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s1",
          "section_path": [
            "Joint comments from Nordic business federations to a Digital Fairness Act"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 47,
          "char_len": 335
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p10",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 5110,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "According to the European Commission, the effectiveness of EU consumer protection is undermined by: Insufficient enforcement, legal uncertainty, increasing risk of regulatory fragmentation across Member States' national approaches and the lack of incentives for businesses to aim for the highest standard of protection.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s1",
          "section_path": [
            "Joint comments from Nordic business federations to a Digital Fairness Act"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 43,
          "char_len": 319
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p11",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3066,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The Nordic confederations: the Confederation of Danish Industry (DI), the Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise (NHO), the Confederation of Swedish Enterprises (Svenskt Näringsliv), and the Confederation of Finnish Industries (EK) have the following key messages regarding such a Digital Fairness Act:",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s1",
          "section_path": [
            "Joint comments from Nordic business federations to a Digital Fairness Act"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 41,
          "char_len": 301
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p12",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3175,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Well-functioning digital markets can provide consumers with the necessary skills and access, with greater choice and more complete information to make informed decisions. New technologies hold the promise of improving consumers' lives.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "About digital markets"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 32,
          "char_len": 235
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p13",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3989,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Before entering a lawmaking process the question must be answered if there is a need for a Digital Fairness Act. The answer is yes, only if there is a gap, meaning a complete or partial absence of effective legal norms protecting European consumers online and if the absence of such norms leads to a market failure. The root cause of such market failure needs to be clearly defined as a gap that needs to be remedied through legislation.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 78,
          "char_len": 437
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p14",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 7611,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "We have so far not seen evidence of such a market failure and hence we doubt whether there is a need for additional new rules in a Digital Fairness Act. Should the European Commission remain",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?"
          ],
          "span": null,
