          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 6694,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "It is of utmost importance to clearly identify actual legal gaps as opposed to enforcement gaps.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 16,
          "char_len": 96
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p25",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Unfair Contract Terms",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "the Unfair Contract Terms Directive (UCTD)"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 10303,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "There is already a plethora of EU consumer protection legislation in force, e.g. the Unfair Commercial Practices Directive (UCPD), the Consumer Rights Directive (CRD), the Unfair Contract Terms Directive (UCTD) and the recently revised General Product Safety Regulation (GPSR).",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?",
            "Already existing EU-legislation and enforcement gaps"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 40,
          "char_len": 277
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p26",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Digital Rulebook (DSA/DMA)",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "new digital rulebook including the Digital Services Act and the Digital Markets Act"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 12610,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "How consumers deal with online platforms has changed rapidly and the European Commission has acknowledged this shift and introduced the new digital rulebook including the Digital Services Act and the Digital Markets Act to promote fair competition and secure digital spaced for consumers.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?",
            "Already existing EU-legislation and enforcement gaps"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 43,
          "char_len": 288
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p27",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3563,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Considering this already existing EU consumer protection legislation, instead of initiating new legislation focus should be on the potential to improve or rethink the current enforcement regime. A strong, resilient, and efficient enforcement by both the Commission and across all member states in close coordination is needed.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?",
            "Already existing EU-legislation and enforcement gaps"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 47,
          "char_len": 326
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p28",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 4722,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Additional EU legislation must only be proposed, if it is obvious that improving the enforcement regime cannot potentially handle the identified challenges. It seems premature to conclude that new legislation is necessary when there has not yet been a proper evaluation of the new digital rulebook and when there seems to be several ways to improve the enforcement regime of EU consumer law.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?",
            "Already existing EU-legislation and enforcement gaps"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 63,
          "char_len": 391
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p29",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 4731,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "If thorough analysis shows that a Digital Fairness Act is needed, it should have a balanced approach that protects consumers in a targeted manner without burdening companies with disproportionate or unnecessary red tape.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?",
            "Better Regulation and Competitiveness"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 33,
          "char_len": 220
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p30",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 5457,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Proportionality, robust impact assessments, evidence-based regulations, and competitiveness checks must be an obvious part of the EU legislation process. A Digital Fairness Act must be evidence-based, legally clear and targeted with an obvious connection between the political objectives, the identified problems, the proposed solutions and their actual impacts, considering EU businesses' competitiveness.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?",
            "Better Regulation and Competitiveness"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 52,
          "char_len": 406
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p31",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 6075,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "A Digital Fairness Act should be principle-based, and technology-neutral. This is important for ensuring predictability, encouraging innovation, and creating a positive investment and competitive climate.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s6",
          "section_path": [
            "Identification of legal gaps. Do we need a Digital Fairness Act?",
            "Technology neutrality and principle-based legislation"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 25,
          "char_len": 204
        }
      },
